description: Recently sold: $112,451. Great things come in small packages! Check out the virtual video of this charming, turn-key cabin set just 40 feet back from the sand shore of deceptively named "Shallow Lake". With 539 acres, an 85' max depth and 14' of water clarity, Shallow Lake is primarily managed for walleyes and largemouth bass. The abundance of ciscoes means some big fish - including Northerns - are out there waiting for you to catch! Property has been with the same family for 50+ years; the well-maintained 2-bedroom cabin was built in 1990. Sun worshippers will love the sunny, south-facing lakefront lawn, firepit and deck, but the mini-split AC awaits to cool you off inside. Less than 3 hours from the Metro, an hour from Duluth and only 20 minutes to Grand Rapids, this convenient comfy cabin is ready to make your waterfront weekends a breeze!
